		<li class="" id="comment-68794">
			
			
			<p>I had this problem recently as well.  I disassembled my ipod and found that the ribbon cable that hooked up to the hard drive was a bit loose.  After unhooking it, and doing the classic nintendo cartridge clean-by-blowing-on-it method, I put it all back together and it&#8217;s worked fine ever since.</p>
<p>My guess is that by slamming it on the ground or whatever, you&#8217;re just reseating the cable.  Hard drives tend to dislike slamming, so I&#8217;m not sure that&#8217;s a good long term solution but whatever makes you feel good right?</p>
			
			<p class="commentmetadata">posted by <b>Steve</b> on 
			<a href="#comment-68794" title="">4-17-2008 at 11:27 pm</a> </p>

		</li>

	
	
		<li class="alt" id="comment-68797">
			
			
			<p>Yep, that also happened with my non-iPod MP3. Every once and a while, it will freeze (usually between songs), and I hear a &#8220;skipping&#8221; sound. A quick smack with a hand and it&#8217;s all good!!</p>
<p>Technology is amazing, isn&#8217;t it??</p>
			
			<p class="commentmetadata">posted by <b>Erin</b> on 
