			<p>Long ago, back when 5.25&#8243; MFM and RLL drives were the cat&#8217;s meow :-), I was a PC Service Technician for an un-named company, and that was the tech-support approved solution from Seagate for a sticking spindle (which the drive platters rotate on).  Repackage the drive in it&#8217;s original shipping containter, then drop from a height of about 2 feet.  Worked like a charm, and allowed MANY customers to get their lost data back.  Nice to know things really haven&#8217;t changed&#8230;</p>
			
			<p class="commentmetadata">posted by <b>Rich</b> on 
			<a href="#comment-68983" title="">4-18-2008 at 2:13 pm</a> </p>

		</li>

	
	
